      "amount": "1/2 teaspoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "Plant-based Cream",
      "amount": "1 cup"
    },
    {
      "name": "Mantecare",
      "amount": "2 tablespoons"
    },
    {
      "name": "Fresh Parsley",
      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "Chopped"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "In a large Dutch oven, combine the potatoes, water, guanciale, onion, carrots, and celery. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer for 20 minutes.",
    "Add the malt syrup, salt, and black pepper. Stir to combine, then continue to simmer for another 10 minutes.",
    "Using an immersion blender, puree the stew until it is slightly smooth. Alternatively, you can transfer the stew to a blender and blend until smooth, then return it to the pot.",
    "Stir in the plant-based cream and mantecare until the stew is thick and creamy. Season with additional salt and pepper if needed.",
    "Serve the stew hot, garnished with chopped fresh parsley."
  ],
